result.formatted_address: 13號 Ting Kok Rd, Tai Po, Hong Kong
result.name: 果子 Life Cafe | 喇沙摻摻·海南雞飯

reviews.text: Good restaurant with various kinds of Malaysian food available. Prices are rasonable and tastes are good. I order the Malaysian meat bone soup set, and it comes with a small bowl of steam rice. Taste of the soup isn't as strong as the original from Malaysia, and the meat bones are only few small pieces. The drink I pick from the set is coffee, and surprisingly the cream served is hot.

I seldom visit Tai Po district, therefore, I decided to try out something new in this area before watching a theater drama nearby. Life Cafe is a newly open restaurant that serves seemingly mouth-watering Singapore and Malaysia cuisine. Bingo! Life Cafe, I gotta try you!

It took a bit of wait as there was a large group of parents and kids taking a few tables for lunch on a Sunday afternoon, and you know how long they take to finish their meals, and forever to get them leave after finishing their meals. After they left, the queue outside restaurant was cleared immediately.

I ordered this Nasi Goreng for lunch, and was wowed when it was served! Cruncy prawn crackers, sunny side up on fried rice, shrimps, and skewers! Oh my god, all on one plate! What else can I ask for?

The fried rice was lit! It’s so delicious that I couldn’t stop eating it. Even better with the egg yolk from sunny side up.

I would say Life Cafe is really attentive to customers’ needs, as the shrimps were half peeled, so you only have to cut out the shrimps’ heads (if you don’t eat them) and enjoy the shrimps without making a mess or getting your hands dirty! Good work! The shrimps were very fresh, and the chili paste was a nice touch up.

Skewers were so good! Really, I couldn’t ask for more. Meat were tender and flavored with a bit of satay sauce.

This Black Sugar Bubble Milk was very delicious too! Bubbles were thoroughly cooked - soft but chewy. The milk was lit, as in not made with milk powder nor overly sweet. It was better than most of the Taiwanese bubble milk tea shops indeed!
Relaxed atmosphere, nice staff, good laksa and Hainan chicken. Not too pricey.

I have tried few different foods & drinks with my friend tonight. Foods & drinks are delicious & environment is very clean and comfortable. Cost is reasonable. Staffs are very friendly. I m highly recommended this restaurant & will go back again for sure.
SE Asia food, taste acceptable but no surprise. Spacious
